Since `m = max (encode φ) (encode ψ)`, we have `encode φ ≤ m` and `encode ψ ≤ m`. By `monotone_construction`, this means:
- `construction T hT (encode φ) ⊆ construction T hT m`
- `construction T hT (encode ψ) ⊆ construction T hT m`

So `Γ ⊆ construction T hT m` and `Δ ⊆ construction T hT m`, which means `Γ ∪ Δ ⊆ construction T hT m`.

```lean
  have : ↑(Γ ∪ Δ) ⊆ construction T hT m := by
    intro x hx
    simp only [Finset.coe_union, Set.mem_union] at hx
    rcases hx with hxΓ | hxΔ
    · exact monotone_construction (le_max_left _ _) (hΓ₁ hxΓ)
    · exact monotone_construction (le_max_right _ _) (hΔ₁ hxΔ)
```
